02:10:16.298 --> 02:10:25.298
What are some of the advantages of using Cordo over Emacs org mode? You can read it there.

02:10:25.298 --> 02:10:32.298
Absolutely. Yeah, so there's a lot of different ways of taking a document with literate programming.

02:10:32.298 --> 02:10:38.298
Part of that is you have things like Jupyter and mbconvert. You have Jupyter and mbdev.

02:10:38.298 --> 02:10:42.298
You have Cordo. You have R Markdown. You have raw Pandoc.

02:10:42.298 --> 02:10:52.298
You have org mode, which is actually an extension to Emacs, where in your terminal inside Emacs rather than an editor, you can write documents with literate programming.

02:10:52.298 --> 02:11:01.298
Rather than saying what the advantage is, is kind of making it language and location agnostic.

02:11:01.298 --> 02:11:08.298
Whereas Emacs and org mode kind of says you're basically saying like you're going to work inside that format only.

02:11:08.298 --> 02:11:12.298
Cordo is really just plain text, so you could use it in any text editor.

02:11:12.298 --> 02:11:17.298
You could use it without a text editor and just use it inside a terminal if you really wanted to.

02:11:17.298 --> 02:11:21.298
You can use it like really richly inside RStudio and VS Code and inside Jupyter.

02:11:21.298 --> 02:11:26.298
And you're meeting people where they are, as opposed to saying like this is the only way to do it.

02:11:26.298 --> 02:11:30.298
It's like you're allowing different editors and different languages to meet in the middle.

02:11:30.298 --> 02:11:35.298
I will say, though, that I'm not deeply familiar with org mode as a user,

02:11:35.298 --> 02:11:45.298
but I'm aware of like there are other things out there that are great and get things done and just calling out a few of those.

02:11:45.298 --> 02:11:52.298
Thank you. Another upvoted question on Slido was how do we comment align in YAML?

02:11:52.298 --> 02:12:06.298
Yeah. So if you I would typically say I don't add like commenting to YAML code in terms of like I'm always a bit nervous about messing things up.

02:12:06.298 --> 02:12:15.298
You can do a pound sign in front of specific lines and that at least in Cordo appears to comment out that line and it no longer executes.

02:12:15.298 --> 02:12:21.298
But more typically, like if you're trying to say like I'm doing this specific thing and like writing out a description,

02:12:21.298 --> 02:12:26.298
like literate programming of YAML, you might actually just want to put that into a comment below the YAML.

02:12:26.298 --> 02:12:32.298
Like you can do an HTML comment or a hidden code chunk that doesn't display when you render the document.

02:12:32.298 --> 02:12:37.298
But it says this is why I'm using this YAML option as opposed to trying to constrain yourself.

